Odfjell, a Norwegian shipping company, opts for the safer Cape of Good Hope route over the pirate-infested Gulf of Aden.
The Saudi-owned super tanker Sirius Star has been seized by pirates off the African coast, showcasing their evolving tactics.
The pirates' ability to adapt is evident as they target large vessels like the Sirius Star, highlighting the vulnerability of ships in the region.
NATO has not intervened in this incident, emphasizing the challenges of patrolling the vast ocean area where piracy is rampant.
The crew of the hijacked tanker, including British nationals, are currently held captive as international efforts are underway to secure their release.
